Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and stylistic variation in writing style.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper focuses on social media and predicting socio-economic status from writing style.
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions using audio features in addition to text features.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper discusses developing and comparing neural models for prediction.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with social stratification and its relationship to writing style on social media.
